<Author>GregontheLake
<Content>The Top TA Rated Hotel in Dallas?? Booked this hotel based upon prior TA user reviews which ranked this hotel as the top hotel in Dallas. I am rarely disappointed by recommendations from TA users, but am in this case. Just returned from a weekend stay with my wife and on one hand the decor and ambience of the hotel is very good. However, there were a number of service gaffes that I would not expect from a top ranked hotel. On the positive side, the lobby and bar area are well done. We had a smaller room with a king bed and the decor was very attractive and new. So physically, the interior of the hotel is beautiful. However, I had higher expectations of service where the hotel really dropped the ball. Arrived Friday afternoon and room was not ready. OK, and they did call later in the afternoon to let me know when my room was ready. Asked to have our bags which were left with the bellman delivered to the room. Returned to the hotel later to get the room key and found my bags were not in the room. Called the front desk to tell them and was told the bellman would deliver them. They did not arrive. Called again and was told the bellman was unavailable and they would have someone else deliver our bags. Got another call to the room as they then could not find our bags. By this time we were going to be late for our event that evening. Finally the front desk employee brought the bags himself to the room. Went back down to get our car from the valet and we were running late. All parking is done by the valet for a $20 daily fee. There were three valet parkers and one went to get our car and then came back and asked what our name was as he could not locate our car. Another 15 minutes and we are even later for our evening plans. We did not try the spa this trip, but I got such a poor first impression on service and stayed in other midtown hotel properties where I did not experience these service problems that I more than likely will not stay at this hotel again. There is condo construction right next door associated with the Stoneleigh and although we were on the 7th floor, there was sufficient noise even during the evening from surrounding establishments heard from our room. Last comment, while the room was nice. I did not enjoy the placement of the AC vents which oddly enough were across the room from the king size bed but blew directly in our faces while in bed and the vents were not adjustable. Not a huge disappointment, but not deserving of the top ranking of Dallas hotels in my opinion. 
