<Author>kkbenton
<Content>great hotel, not as convenient as staying downtown I'm spending 4 weeks working in downtown Dallas and staying at 4 different hotels. The Stoneleigh is definitely the nicest - the rooms are a step up from the Adolphus, but it was somewhat inconvenient for getting downtown. Its a quick drive, but considering the overnight parking at the Stoneleigh is $21.65 and then daily parking downtown is $15-20, it makes more sense to leave the car at the hotel. That means either cabbing it, taking the bus, or the trolley. The walk involved with the trolley was too far in business clothes and the trolley is not air conditioned (not good in the summer.) You can catch the bus right outside the Stoneleigh and it dropped me off a block from the building, but its a jolting, bumpy ride and you have to have exact change, in cash.IMO, there's a big difference between this hotel and the Adolphus - everything about the Stoneleigh was updated, pristinely clean, and top notch. They did turn down service with chocolates, had these great robes, and flat screen TVs. They actually provided starch with the iron. I really enjoyed the comfortable seating on the front deck. Its also a quick walk down to the Katy Trail and the park on Turtle Creek.Most of the restaurants within walking distance are pretty expensive. We had pizza and salad at Coal Vines for $25/each. It was good, but ouch! Mattitos was good and more reasonable.One issue I had was the design of my room put the bed right next to the door and the room was very close to the elevators, which made for a noise problem. I was also woken up at 4am by a hotel employee using a 2 way radio right outside my door. Check Expedia for prices - it was $130/night for the week I was there. 
