<Content>Great hotel - Renovated I just finished a 3 night stay at the Stoneleigh Hotel  Spa in Dallas. I booked the hotel from their website and booked a Studio Suite. I had to come into town for a meeting and also to do some shopping before heading to New York.I was flying from Buenos Aires and the flight got in very early at 7 AM. I emailed ahead of time and asked if I could check-in early and one of the managers, Anita, confirmed it would be fine. The hotel is in a great area conveniently located in the Uptown Area. It鈥檚 very close to downtown and also you have quick access to the Tollway and also Highway 75. It鈥檚 also close to Highland Park where my friend lives so it was convenient.The hotel has recently been renovated and the hotel got a nice write up in the Wall Street Journal last week. They just finished a $36 million renovation. The lobby isn鈥檛 anything over the top but nice. I never stayed at the hotel before the renovation so I can鈥檛 compare it to before but it鈥檚 nice.My room was very big with 4 large windows, a king size bed, a big 46鈥?high definition TV, nice bathroom and a walk in closet with plenty of room. The bed was very comfortable as well.  My air conditioning wasn鈥檛 working right the first day and I complained and they sent up a maintenance worker right away and he confirmed it was just blowing air and fixed it. The staff was always very friendly. My only complaint/problem was the first day I called down to ask for some razors to shave (I forgot to pack them). The front desk confirmed they would send someone up with some. They never did even after 3 calls down to the desk. They kept saying, 鈥渟omeone is on their way up鈥?but they never came. I would have just preferred them saying they didn鈥檛 have any if they didn鈥檛. Also, the biggest problem is the valet parking area. It鈥檚 extremely small and not well organized. Most people coming in town will probably have a rental car as taxis aren鈥檛 too common in Dallas compared to other large cities. They charge u$s 21 per day for parking which is common in hotels in this area. The problem is that people come to the hotel for dinner to eat or to have drinks in the bar so that parking area is a total zoo. The guys seem to try but they had some problems. I called down to have my car ready and sometimes they didn鈥檛 have it ready and one night I had to wait almost 20 minutes for my car. 1 time they couldn鈥檛 find my keys. Also, the night that it was really hectic was a Friday and I went out and drove to nearby Highland Park to pick up a friend for dinner and I noticed the valet guys left someone else鈥檚 car keys in my front seat! Fortunately I was going to dinner at Craft which was close by so I stopped by the hotel to drop off the keys. I can鈥檛 imagine if I didn鈥檛 notice them and bring them back what the hotel would have done for this guest/customer if they wanted to leave. I found this a bit troubling.Really the only complaint I had was the valet parking situation but the hotel was great. One thing to note is they are building a building next door to the hotel so there is a bit of noise in the morning and throughout the day. If you want to sleep in and are a light sleeper, keep this in mind.All in all a great hotel with friendly staff and comfortable rooms. 
